maLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:338:"Today we are happy to announce a few compatible WPML themes. The themes are, Striking Multiflex, PE Beauty Center, PrimeTrans, Agile If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here: Multilingual Ready Themes Multilingual Ready Plugins Also, if you’re a theme or a [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4700:"<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-975307" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WPML-Compatible-themes-1-300x84.png" alt="WPML Compatible themes" width="400" height="112" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WPML-Compatible-themes-1-300x84.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WPML-Compatible-themes-1-150x42.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WPML-Compatible-themes-1.png 568w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>\n<p>Today we are happy to announce a few compatible WPML themes.</p>\n<p>The themes are, <a href="https://themeforest.net/item/striking-multiflex-ecommerce-responsive-wp-theme/128763" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Striking Multiflex</a>, <a href="https://www.pixelemu.com/themes/i/40-fashion-beauty/7-pe-beauty-center" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PE Beauty Center</a>, <a href="https://themeforest.net/item/primetrans-logistics-wordpress-theme/14122657" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PrimeTrans</a>, <a href="https://themeforest.net/item/agile-lightweight-blogging-and-shopping-wordpress-theme/16122474" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Agile</a></p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you’re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process, we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin Multilingual Ready.</p>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Striking Multiflex</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Striking MulitFlex is a powerful and flexible wordpress theme featuring a framework that can scale for large sites and web requirements.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://themeforest.net/item/striking-multiflex-ecommerce-responsive-wp-theme/128763" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Purchase Striking Multiflex</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">PE Beauty Center</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Premium WordPress theme for professions like hairdresser, massage salon, spa center, fashion stylist, manicure or even fitness gym.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://www.pixelemu.com/themes/i/40-fashion-beauty/7-pe-beauty-center" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download PE Beauty Center</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">PrimeTrans</h2>\n<blockquote><p>PrimeTrans is Fully Responsive, Retina-Ready clean and flexible logistics WordPress Theme</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://themeforest.net/item/primetrans-logistics-wordpress-theme/14122657" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Purchase PrimeTrans</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Agile</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Agile is a clean, simple and lightweight WordPress theme suitable for Blogging and Online Shopping</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://themeforest.net/item/agile-lightweight-blogging-and-shopping-wordpress-theme/16122474" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Purchase Agile</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=uRQPbnp_FxE:yU7T2FhUXaM:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/uRQPbnp_FxE" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://wpml.org/2016/09/compatible-themes-sep-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"https://wpml.org/2016/09/compatible-themes-sep-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"How to build multilingual real estate sites with Toolset and WPML";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/pcBn16RoWw8/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/build-multilingual-real-estate-sites-toolset-wpml/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 14:48:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://wpml.org/?p=1046119";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:341:"Building a fully multilingual real estate site can be challenging. In this post, we teach how you can do it using Toolset plugins. You can start from scratch, or by using a complete reference design to speed up development. What our multilingual real estate site will include &#8220;Real estate&#8221; is anything that you build on [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Amir";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17387:"<p><strong>Building a fully multilingual real estate site can be challenging. In this post, we teach how you can do it using <a href="https://wp-types.com/">Toolset</a> plugins. You can start from scratch, or by using a complete reference design to speed up development.</strong></p>\n<h2>What our multilingual real estate site will include</h2>\n<p>&#8220;Real estate&#8221; is anything that you build on the ground, including just land (without anything built on it). Apartments, buildings, open land and offices have different fields and display differently. For this reason, we&#8217;ve decided to create a separate <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/create-a-custom-post-type/">custom post type</a> for each of them.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046126" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600.jpg" alt="real-estate-home-600" width="600" height="623" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600-144x150.jpg 144w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600-289x300.jpg 289w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>Each section in the site includes its own slider, with featured items and <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/front-page-filters/">custom search</a>. The custom search allows to find items according to their attributes (like size, price and features). It displays the results as a grid (textual list) and as markers on a Google Map.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046155" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600.jpg" alt="custom-search-houses-600" width="600" height="781" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600-115x150.jpg 115w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600-230x300.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>Each item displays with full details, including the listing agent, features and location on map.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046171" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600.jpg" alt="single-house-600" width="600" height="606" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600-297x300.jpg 297w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600-90x90.jpg 90w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>So, if you&#8217;re going to build such a site yourself, you should:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create the custom post types and their fields and taxonomy</li>\n<li>Find how to implement a custom search (which is a major part of the project)</li>\n<li>Find how to display items on a Google Map</li>\n<li>Design how everything should display</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to build a multilingual real estate site with Toolset</h2>\n<p>There are great themes that will do this for you. Today, we will explain how to build such sites using our <a href="https://wp-types.com">Toolset</a> plugins.</p>\n<p>In case you haven&#8217;t heard about Toolset, it&#8217;s a package of plugins that help you build advanced sites with custom types, without programming. Toolset is a great fit for real estate sites because they rely heavily on custom post types and <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/using-custom-fields/">custom fields</a>. With Toolset, it&#8217;s easy to set up these custom types and fields and display them nicely on the front-end, without writing PHP.</p>\n<h3>Custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate site</h3>\n<p>The first thing that we did was create the custom post types, custom fields and taxonomy. Even though the site looks simple, it has 7 different custom post types. Go to <strong>Toolset-&gt;Dashboard</strong> to create them.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046452" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046452" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-300x267.png" alt="The custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate reference site" width="300" height="267" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-300x267.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-150x133.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-768x682.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-1024x910.png 1024w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site.png 1129w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate reference site</p></div>\n<p>We created separate sets of custom fields, which add the attributes that each custom post type needs.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046474" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046474" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-300x272.png" alt="Custom fields for apartments" width="300" height="272" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-300x272.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-150x136.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments.png 537w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Custom fields for apartments</p></div>\n<h3>Designing the site&#8217;s front-end with Toolset</h3>\n<p>Our front-end design center with Toolset is <strong>Layouts</strong> plugin. Layouts allows to design the &#8220;wireframe&#8221; of your site with a drag-and-drop editor. Then, you build the details of each of the blocks using <strong>Views</strong> plugin.</p>\n<p>First, you design the layout. You will start with the parent layout, which includes the elements that appear on each page in the site.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046543" style="width: 277px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046543" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-267x300.png" alt="The master layout of site, including the header, footer and placeholder for child layouts" width="267" height="300" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-267x300.png 267w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-134x150.png 134w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-768x862.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout.png 836w" sizes="(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The master layout of site, including the header, footer and placeholder for child layouts</p></div>\n<p>Then, you proceed with the design of the layouts (wireframes) for different main pages. This is the layout for the &#8220;houses archive&#8221;, which is the search page for houses.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046517" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046517" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-300x294.png" alt="Houses archive layout (the &quot;wireframe&quot; for the list of houses)" width="300" height="294" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-300x294.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-150x147.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-768x753.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout.png 833w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Houses archive layout (the &#8220;wireframe&#8221; for the list of houses)</p></div>\n<p>Once you have the layouts ready, it&#8217;s time to dive into the different blocks and build them. You will do this with <strong>Views</strong>. A View loads content from the database and displays it. You can create Views for simple lists, sliders, custom searches, tables, grids and anything that you can think of.</p>\n<p>Building a View takes three steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select what the View is for (simple list, custom search, paginated list, slider)</li>\n<li>Choose more options, depending on the kind of View that you&#8217;re creating</li>\n<li>Design the output using HTML and CSS</li>\n</ol>\n<div id="attachment_1046598" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046598" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-300x148.png" alt="Setting up a View - 1. Choose which content to display" width="300" height="148" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-300x148.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-150x74.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection.png 702w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 1. choose which content to display</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_1046610" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046610" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-300x116.png" alt="Setting up a View - 2. Select options for that kind of View" width="300" height="116" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-300x116.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-150x58.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting.png 685w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 2. choose options for that kind of View</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_1046621" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046621" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-300x183.png" alt="Setting up a View - 3. Design the output using HTML" width="300" height="183" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-300x183.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-150x91.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor.png 738w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 3. Design the output using HTML</p></div>\n<p>You may have noticed that the HTML code above uses shortcodes. These shortcodes display fields. You don&#8217;t need to memorize shortcodes or their options. To include a field in the HTML, click on the <strong>Fields and Views</strong> button in the editor. Select the field, enter its options and you get the completed shortcode.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046801" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046801" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-300x266.png" alt="Inserting a field" width="300" height="266" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-300x266.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-150x133.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field.png 544w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Inserting a field</p></div>\n<p>This way, you can create your own custom layouts and inside them, build the site-elements that you need. If you can write HTML and CSS, you can achieve anything with Toolset, without writing PHP.</p>\n<h2>How to translate</h2>\n<p>One of the great things about Toolset is the seamless integration with WPML. Anything that you create with Toolset is trivial to translate with WPML.</p>\n<p>Toolset automatically registers all &#8220;strings&#8221; for translation.</p>\n<p>When you go to <strong>WPML-&gt;String translation</strong>, you will see string domains for each of the Views (and other Toolset elements) that you created. There will also be domains for the custom post types and fields.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046871" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046871" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-300x212.png" alt="Translating the strings in a View" width="300" height="212" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-300x212.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-150x106.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-768x541.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view.png 912w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating the strings in a View</p></div>\n<p>Translating layouts is even easier. Go to <strong>WPML-&gt;Translation management</strong> and you will see <strong>Layouts</strong> appearing in the <strong>Translation dashboard</strong>.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046903" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046903" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-300x233.png" alt="Layouts to translate" width="300" height="233" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-300x233.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-150x117.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-768x598.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate.png 825w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Layouts to translate</p></div>\n<p>Translating a layout is similar to translating posts. You will get a list of texts which appear in the layout and translate just them. You don&#8217;t need to recreate layouts separately per language.</p>\n<h2>Start from scratch or from a complete working reference site</h2>\n<p>With Toolset, you can create your own multilingual real estate sites completely from scratch. You can also use our complete <a href="http://discover-wp.com/site-types/bootstrap-estate/">real estate reference</a> site as a starting point. Since our reference site is completely built using Toolset plugins, you can modify anything in it. You can edit element, remove and add your own.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/pcBn16RoWw8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s: